<br>
You are correct about the UN by itself being powerless.  I should have made that clear in my post.  My point was that it actually has significant power inside the US because of the treaties having legal meaning through which the government can be subject to legal action.<br>
<br>
All it takes is the the US to breach those treaties and the government/military can be dragged through court and end up invalidating any evidence that may have been gathered from the prisoners - all of which would need to be used in a criminal trial at some later stage.  Even worse, the courts could demand the government set the prisoners free without trial for improper arrest/imprisonment etc.<br>
<br>
I'm just saying that these people not only deserve to be treated as humans, but should actually be treated with kiddy gloves to ensure that no spectre of impropriety can be cast on who is in the right and who is in the wrong.  The government and military are not above the law in the US.<br>
<br>
My greatest fear at the present time is not that some of these petty terrorists escape, but that the balances detailed in the consitution will be usurped in a fervor of paranoia and suspicion.  It worries me when Time magazine and others post editorials on how measures like national ID cards would help matters when these terrorists who flew the planes into the WTC were legally inside the US and would have had the same ID cards as every other legal alien.  Honestly, I actually don't have too much against an ID card, it just won't prevent terrorism.<br>
<br>
It worries me when I see laws passed that allow me to be imprisioned indefinitely without trial on suspicion of being a terrorist.  I'm a legal alien.  I use a boxcutter at work.  I enjoy flight simulators.  Maybe I should just hand myself in right now?  <br>
<br>
Is the US still the land of the free and the home of the brave when laws are passed restricting freedoms out of fear?<br>
<br>
Ddrak <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm58.showPrevMessage?topicID=599.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm58.showNextMessage?topicID=599.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm58.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=599.topic&index=42><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~eqmaximus/brell/addreply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm58.threadControl?topicID=599.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm58.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=599.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm58.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=599.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="brellserilisfrm70">News and Events<option value="brellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion">The Commons (General EQ Discussion)<option value="brellserilisfrm58">The Outer Realm (Off Topic)<option value="brellserilisfrm56">The Hall of Honor<option value="brellserilisroleplaying">The Tavern (Roleplaying)<option value="brellserilisfrm55">The Fellowship of Guilds<option value="brellserilisfrm53">The Valley of Rest (Retirements)<option value="brellserilisfrm66">The Back Alley (Link to Rants)<option v